Class ManageRegisteredServicesMultiActionController

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jasig.cas.services.web.ManageRegisteredServicesMultiActionController

  • @Controller
public final class ManageRegisteredServicesMultiActionController
extends Object
    MultiActionController to handle the deletion of RegisteredServices as well as displaying them on the Manage Services page.

    3.1
    Author:
    Scott Battaglia

      • updateRegisteredServiceEvaluationOrder

        @RequestMapping(value="updateRegisteredServiceEvaluationOrder.html",

public org.springframework.web.servlet.ModelAndView updateRegisteredServiceEvaluationOrder(@RequestParam(value="id")
                                                                                                 long id,
                                                                                                 @RequestParam(value="evaluationOrder")
                                                                                                 int evaluationOrder)
        Updates the RegisteredService.getEvaluationOrder(). Expects an id parameter to indicate the RegisteredService.getId() and the new evaluationOrder integer parameter from the request. as parameters.
        Parameters:
        id - the id
        evaluationOrder - the evaluation order
        Returns:
        ModelAndView object that redirects to a jsonView. The model will contain a a parameter error whose value should describe the error occurred if the update is unsuccessful. There will also be a successful boolean parameter that indicates whether or not the update was successful.
